Parent update → child re-render by default. React re-renders whole subtree unless told not to.

**Common causes:**
- No memoization — wrap component in `React.memo()`
- New object/array/fn prop each render — parent creates `{}` or `[]` inline → new ref every time → memo useless
- Context change — any context consumer re-renders when value changes

**Fixes:**
```js
// Memoize component
const Child = React.memo(({ data }) => { ... });

// Stabilize object/array props
const data = useMemo(() => ({ id, name }), [id, name]);

// Stabilize function props
const handleClick = useCallback(() => doThing(id), [id]);
```

**Debug:** React DevTools Profiler → "Highlight updates" shows what re-renders + why.

